OAB - The study examined links between fat stored in the liver, small brain lesions, 
      and cognitive skills, such as memory. The results indicated that people with more 
      liver fat had more small lesions in the brain and that they did not perform as 
      well on cognitive tests as people with less fat in the liver. Therefore, reducing 
      fat in the liver may be beneficial to avoid cognitive decline resulting from 
      small brain lesions.
