JID - 101564430
SB  - IM
OAB - In this nationwide study of women in Korea, researchers found that having an 
      excess buildup of liver fat linked to metabolic issues was associated with a 
      higher risk of heart attack, stroke, and cardiovascular death. The absolute 
      increase in this risk was notably larger in postmenopausal women compared to 
      those who had not yet gone through menopause. Cardiovascular risk progressively 
      increased as the severity of liver fat accumulation worsened, a pattern observed 
      regardless of menopausal status.The 5-year absolute risk difference tied to this 
      liver condition was more than twice as large in postmenopausal women.
